'\"
'\" XCursor extension manual page
'\"
.TH xcursor n 1.0 "XCursor Extension"
.BS
.SH NAME
xcursor \- apply X Cursor library cursor files to Tk windows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
\fBpackage require XCursor\fR
.sp
\fBxcursor\fI window filepath\fR
.fi
.BE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The \fBxcursor\fR command loads cursor images from files in the Xcursor
format and applies them to Tk windows.
.PP
Cursor files are typically found in system icon themes under directories
like \fI/usr/share/icons/*/cursors/\fR.
.SH COMMAND
.TP
\fBxcursor\fI window filepath\fR
Applies the cursor loaded from \fIfilepath\fR to \fIwindow\fR.
If \fIfilepath\fR is an empty string, removes any custom cursor
and restores the default.
.PP
The command caches loaded cursors internally. Loading the same
file multiple times reuses the cached cursor.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Apply a cursor from the system theme:
.CS
xcursor . /usr/share/icons/Adwaita/cursors/hand1
.CE
.PP
Remove custom cursor:
.CS
xcursor . ""
.CE
.PP
Different cursors on different widgets:
.CS
button .btn
entry .ent
xcursor .btn /usr/share/icons/default/cursors/hand2
xcursor .ent /usr/share/icons/default/cursors/xterm
.CE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
cursor(n), Tk_DefineCursor(3)
.SH KEYWORDS
cursor, X11, Xcursor
